sbol:Collection.dcterms:title: iGEM Parts Registry
sbol:Collection.dcterms:description: The iGEM Registry is a growing collection of genetic parts that can be mixed and matched to build synthetic biology devices and systems. As part of the synthetic biology community's efforts to make biology easier to engineer, it provides a source of genetic parts to iGEM teams and academic labs.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K101005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Construct with LacI/LAMBDAcI promoter, RBS, GFP, Terminator
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Has a promoter which is dually repressed by LacI and LAMBDAcI. The RBS is the ribosomal binding site. The GFP is a green fluorescent protein, which is a reporter gene. The Terminator is used to terminate RNA polymerase's transcription.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Ellen Martin
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This construct is composed of: LacI promoter ( R0010), LAMBDAcI promoter (R0051), RBS (B0032), GFP (E0040), and Terminator (B1006).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Majority of design considerations were dealt with during the design of the dually repressed promoter (K101001). A medium strength RBS was used to increase the affinity of this part for ribosomal binding. Additionally, this decision was made to use only a single terminator.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K101001
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Dual-Repressed Promoter for LacI and LambdacI
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This part is a new construct of a promoter that is dually repressed by either LacI or LambdacI proteins.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Bennett Swiniarski
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This part was made by combining BioBrick parts R0010(LacI promoter) and R0051 (LambdacI promoter), along with intermediate sequence between these operator sites.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: LambdacI usually binds to two operator sites, one located upstream from -35 and one located between -35 and -10. By itself, LacI binds downstream from -10. This made the part design very straightforward, since the locations of the operator sites do not overlap at all. In order to complete this part, we simply combined the proper sequences and we had a dually-repressed promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0032
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Weak1 RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0030</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("RBS-2" in figure 4-14 of thesis).

Contact info for this part: Brian Chow

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B1006
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Artificial terminator, estimated %T~>90% *8bp stem, 6nt loop *Bidirectional, estimated reverse %T~>90%
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Haiyao Huang
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: modified E. coli thr terminator, replaced all A-T pairs in stem with C-G pairs
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Bidirectional, with the reverse estimated to be less effective than the forward. Has a polyA tail of 9 residues.
